---
import { ChevronDown, ExternalLink } from "lucide-astro";
import { website } from "../seo";
---

<!-- Data written directly in markup for maximum flexibility (no frontmatter) -->
<section
  class="pt-16 pb-16 lg:flex lg:items-start lg:gap-x-20"
  id="collaborate"
>
  <header
    class="mb-16 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-4 justify-between lg:flex-col lg:items-start"
  >
    <h2 class="text-lg sm:text-2xl lg:text-3xl text-balance !leading-[1.54]">
      Lets Built Together! Worst case scenario, we only have a great
      conversation.
    </h2>

    <a
      href={`mailto:${website.email}`}
      class="px-0 flex gap-x-1 mt-4 text-sm hover:underline underline-offset-2 text-nowrap"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      {`Write me an email`}
      <ExternalLink class="size-4 stroke-current" />
    </a>
  </header>

  <div id="collaboration-faq" class="grow accordion-container lg:max-w-md">
    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          How do I get in touch?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Just send a message via my <a href="#" class="underline">socials</a>.
          Tell me what you're trying to build or fix. No corporate nonsense — if
          it’s a good fit, we’ll talk. If not, I’ll point you in the right
          direction.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          What services do you offer?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          I solve problems with software. Most of my work sits in web apps,
          dashboards, internal tools, automation and platform infrastructure. If
          you have a process that’s manual, inefficient, or non-existent — I can
          design and build the system to handle it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          Do you only build websites and frontend?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          No — I build products, not just pages. I work on anything from landing
          pages to full platforms with authentication, databases, payments,
          messaging or real-time features. If it runs in the browser or on a
          server, I can make it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          How do projects with you usually work?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          You tell me what problem you're trying to solve. We define the core
          outcome, strip out the noise, and I propose the fastest path to
          execution. Depending on the project, I’ll either work independently or
          closely with you in short feedback loops.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          What technologies do you specialize in?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Modern JavaScript (Next.js, React, Node.js) for most builds. I also
          use databases like Postgres or MongoDB depending on the use case. Even
          Copilot AI! I’m flexible — tech is a tool, not a religion.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ac">
      <h4 class="ac-header">
        <button type="button" class="ac-trigger">
          I'm not technical. Is that a problem?
          <ChevronDown
            class="h-4 w-4 shrink-0 text-muted-foreground transition-transform duration-200"
          />
        </button>
      </h4>
      <div class="ac-panel" role="region">
        <p>
          Nope. Your job is to explain the goal in plain language. My job is to
          translate it into logic, features, and delivery. If you’re technical,
          great — we speak code. If not, I’ll keep it simple.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #collaboration-faq .ac-container,
  #collaboration-faq .ac,
  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger {
    background: transparent;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger {
    border: none;
    display: flex;
    flex: 1;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    text-align: start;
    cursor: pointer;
    @apply text-foreground text-base font-medium sm:text-lg;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger:focus,
  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger:hover {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger::after {
    content: "";
    display: none;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-trigger[aria-expanded="true"] svg {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-content {
    overflow: hidden;
    animation-duration: 0.2s;
    animation-timing-function: ease-out;
    animation-fill-mode: forwards;
    padding-inline: 0px;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel {
    @apply font-sans !text-sm;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel > *:first-child {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  #collaboration-faq .ac-panel > *:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac-content[data-state="open"] {
    animation-name: accordion-down;
  }

  #collaboration-faq .ac {
    @apply border-x-transparent border-t-transparent border-b border-b-muted-foreground/15;
  }
</style>

<script>
  import Accordion from "accordion-js";
  import "accordion-js/dist/accordion.min.css";

  new Accordion("#collaboration-faq", {
    duration: 300,
    showMultiple: false,
    collapse: true,
    openOnInit: [0],
  });
</script>
